    • Enum Constant Detail

      • VERSION_1

        public static final WffBinaryMessageUtil VERSION_1
        A wff binary message is a collection of name-value pairs where both name and value can be a binary data. It can have duplicate names.
        The wff binary message is composed as follows :-
        The first byte represents the maximum number of bytes for name length bytes. The second byte represents the maximum number of bytes for the value length bytes. The remaining bytes represent the name-value pairs. 
         Name value pair :-

 
        
 
        
 name length bytes
 name bytes
 value length bytes
 value bytes
        Here, the name length bytes is the length of name bytes and value length bytes is the length of value bytes.
        If the value bytes is an array of values then each value is prepended with length of value and will be appended with char A. 
         Value as an array :-
 
        
 
        
 total value length bytes
 value length bytes
 value bytes
 value length bytes
 value bytes
 A
 
        
 
        

 Here, total value length bytes = sum of (value length bytes + value bytes + value length bytes + value bytes) no. of bytes.
 And, A is represented as the extra identifier byte which represents the value as an array. The total value length bytes doesn't include the length of A.
